# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TeleBotHost MCP Server — Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# OPTIONAL: TeleBotHost Developer API key (used as server-side fallback).
#
# In most setups you should NOT set this. Instead, each MCP client should pass
# its own TBH API key per-request via the "X-Tbh-Api-Key" header. This way:
#   - Each user uses their own TBH quota
#   - The server doesn't store anyone's secret key
#   - Multiple users can share one MCP deployment
#
# Only set this if:
#   - You're self-hosting for a single user (personal use)
#   - You want a fallback for requests that don't include a per-call key
#
# Get your key from: https://telebothost.com → Developer Settings → API Keys
#   sk_*  = secret key (full write access) — keep private
#   pub_* = public key (read-only) — safe for client-side
#
# TELEBOTHOST_API_KEY=sk_your_secret_key_here

# OPTIONAL: Override the API base URL (defaults to https://api.telebothost.com/api/v1)
# TELEBOTHOST_API_BASE=https://api.telebothost.com/api/v1

# OPTIONAL: Protect your MCP endpoint with a shared secret.
# If set, clients must send "Authorization: Bearer <MCP_AUTH_TOKEN>" to access
# the MCP. This is separate from the TBH API key — use it when you want to
# restrict WHO can call your MCP, regardless of which TBH key they pass.
# MCP_AUTH_TOKEN=your-mcp-access-token

# OPTIONAL: Port for the generic Node server (server.ts).
# Auto-set by Render/Railway/Fly. Defaults to 3000 for local dev.
# PORT=3000
